Triad Networks

Tim Vigers

08 April 2020

Graph Structures

Optimal Bayesian network structures for 7157 metabolite-methylation-T1D triads (selected from linear models) were determined using a hill climbing algorithm based on BIC. There are a total of 24 possible network structures for each triad, and in total the selected triads contain 6467 unique methylation sites and 76 unique metabolites.

Results

Of the 24 possible network structures, only 10 were picked using the hill-climbing algorithm.

Three arcs

Total three-arc graphs: 74

Two arcs

Total two-arc graphs: 2782

One arc

Total one-arc graphs: 3794
